        <div class="question">
            <h3>II. Explanation of Input Elements in addEmployee.html</h3>
            <p>
                The addEmployee.html file contains a form for adding employee information. It includes the following input elements:
            </p>
            <p>
                The <strong>First Name</strong> input field allows users to enter the employee's first name.
            </p>
            <p>
                The <strong>Last Name</strong> input field allows users to enter the employee's last name.
            </p>
            <p>
                The <strong>Email</strong> input field allows users to enter the employee's email address.
            </p>
            <p>
                The <strong>Address</strong> input field allows users to enter the employee's address.
            </p>
            <p>
                The <strong>Enrollment Status</strong> dropdown menu enables users to select the employee's enrollment status from a list of options.
            </p>
            <p>
                The <strong>Course ID</strong> input field allows users to enter the employee's course ID.
            </p>
        </div>

        <div class="question">
            <h3>III. Return Value from checkLastName() Function</h3>
            <p>
                The checkLastName() function is responsible for validating the last name input in addEmployee.html. It returns a boolean value:
            </p>
            <p>
                If the last name contains non-alphabetic characters, the function returns <strong>False</strong> and triggers an error alert.
            </p>
            <p>
                If the last name consists only of alphabetic characters, the function returns <strong>True</strong>, allowing the form submission to proceed.
            </p>
            <p>
